--POST request
{
  "name": "Craze Children School",
  "address": "Khadakwasla, Pune",
  "latitude": 15.1204,
  "longitude": 83.1567
}

--GET request

http://localhost:3000/listSchools?latitude=15.1204&longitude=83.1567

GET /listSchools
This endpoint retrieves a list of schools based on the provided latitude and longitude.
Request Parameters
latitude (number) - The latitude coordinate for the location.
longitude (number) - The longitude coordinate for the location.

Response
Upon a successful request, the server responds with a status code of 200 and a JSON array containing school objects with the following properties:
id (number) - The unique identifier for the school.
name (string) - The name of the school.
address (string) - The address of the school.
latitude (number) - The latitude coordinate of the school location.
longitude (number) - The longitude coordinate of the school location.
distance (number) - The distance of the school from the provided latitude and longitude coordinates.

In the example response, the actual values for the properties are masked for privacy.


